m/a/80QqfbN</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[SpottieOttieDopaliciousAngel]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Former aircraft carrier USS Kitty Hawk headed to the scrapyard today [OC]</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/8nu3XW2</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/KmoW8vs.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Former aircraft carrier USS Kitty Hawk, drifting through the fog like a ghost ship, departing Bremerton for the last time today.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/kpXIJst.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I will be cutting together a short video with a lot more detail in the coming days. You can see it on my youtube channel or instagram at @atomicaerials

Thanks imgur!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ISMJ5o4.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Launched in 1960, she served for 49 years before being decommissioned and joining the reserve fleet of inactive vessels at Puget Sound Naval Yard. First of her class but last to be decommissioned, she is the last existing non-nuclear powered aircraft carrier.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/LHUTGLw.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The last carrier of her class to be decommissioned, her fate is to be towed to Brownsville, Texas by Foss Maritime Company for scrapping. She became the sole responsibility of the scrapping company as soon as she left the naval yard. As her beam is too wide for the Panama Canal, Foss has the duty of taking her clear down to the tip of South America, through the Strait of Magellan, and back up to the Gulf Coast.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/lTSNRiA.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>If you look closely here, you can see her four propellers have been removed and are sitting on the rear of the flight deck.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/aPqRFtJ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This trip will take at least 129 days, cover more than 16,000 miles, and take three separate crews, changed out in Valparaiso and Trinidad. Her towed speed will be somewhere between 5 and 8 knots, depending on weather.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/jEu6h86.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The tug towing her here is the Lindsey Foss, a 155' long fire-fighting tractor tug that usually spends most of her time escorting oil tankers in and out of Puget Sound. She is fitted with a Voith-Schneider drive, basically two "cyclorotors" that look like eggbeaters that allow her to change direction without a rudder. This drive is particularly interesting as it allows a tug to "crabwalk" sideways. Shortly after the Lindsey towed Kitty Hawk into the Sound, that carrier was handed over to the slightly-smaller Michelle Foss for the journey to Texas.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/7Vd9BUZ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This was a really amazing event to shoot, unfortunately the fog was so low that I couldn't get a clear shot above the flight deck, and several times the superstructure disappeared entirely into the fog.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/8nu3XW2</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[AtomicAerials]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Barney's dance abilities</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/0fszBYV</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/iYZ4NkD.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/0fszBYV</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[jfolks01]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Choosing his starter</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/jCwsnjb</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/cdx9c2e.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>#pokemon</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/jCwsnjb</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[msinclair02]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Quebec's jaywalking billboard in a bus stop...</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/0GBHEQV</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/fCd8Xob.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/0GBHEQV</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ImpatientMoth]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>If it is not a fake , then you will feel an inner satisfaction.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/905jRX0</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.